## 🔄 Complete Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as React Client (Applications.jsx)
    participant Server as Express Server
    participant DB as MongoDB (JobApplication.js)
    participant Groq as Groq AI (llama-3.1-8b-instant)

    Client->>Server: POST /api/applications (form with resumeId, jobDescription, etc.)
    Server->>Server: calculateMatch(resumeText, jobDescription)
    Server->>Groq: explainMatchWithAI({ matchPercentage, matchedKeywords, missingKeywords, ... })
    Groq-->>Server: JSON response (verdict, quickWins, missingSkillsContext, shouldApply)
    Server->>DB: Save new JobApplication with aiExplanation
    DB-->>Server: Saved Document
    Server-->>Client: 201 Created (document populated with resume info + aiExplanation)
    Client->>Client: Add to application list state & expand advice card automatically
```

---

## 🛠️ Manual Setup Steps
No new database migration or NPM dependency installation is strictly required. If there are existing applications in the database, their `aiExplanation.verdict` will default to `""`, causing the "See AI Advice" button to be hidden automatically as expected.

---

## 🧪 Manual Testing Guide

### 1. Test Single Analyze Matching
- Perform `POST /api/match/analyze` with a payload of `{ resumeId, jobDescription }`.
- Ensure the JSON response now includes an `aiExplanation` object.

### 2. Test Creating an Application
- On the **Applications** page, fill in a resume, title, company, and JD, and save the application.
- Verify that:
  - The application card appears at the top of the list.
  - The card is **automatically expanded** to reveal the AI Advice box.
  - The Advice box shows the custom icon, verdict string, and the color-coded pill (`Apply ✓` in green or `Tailor First` in amber).
  - Quick wins and missing skills are listed cleanly.

### 3. Test Collapsing & Expanding
- Click **✦ Hide Advice** to collapse the AI box.
- Click **✦ See AI Advice** to expand it again.
- Verify that expanding and collapsing states are isolated per-card and do not affect neighboring application cards.
